{"TopicId":150869,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Help me launch this Shuttle","CreatedByName":"DarkFighter","CreatedById":168628,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T11:06:55Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"DarkFighter","CreatedById":168628,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T11:06:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello, fellows!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn my 1.1.2 career I need to rescue somebody with his debris from the orbit of the Mun. I don\u0027t want\u00A0to build sth. with a 10m heatshield, grabbing the debris and then landing on Kerbin. I want to do a shuttle with a cargo bay. I could install some 2.5m cargo bay mods but that is too easy and after 1,5 years KSP playtime I\u0027m still new to the topic \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI came up with this:\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/4uu21mghca24r3k/MK3%20Shuttle.craft?dl=0\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.dropbox.com/s/4uu21mghca24r3k/MK3 Shuttle.craft?dl=0\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut every time I launch, if with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E or only \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E it keeps falling to the side. What do I do wrong?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks for the help\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-26T11:07:46Z\u0022 title=\u002210/26/2016 11:07  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DarkFighter\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Firemetal","CreatedById":164725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T12:07:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPics?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFire\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DarkFighter","CreatedById":168628,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T12:27:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222824123\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022150869\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221477483670\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022164725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Firemetal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, Firemetal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPics?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFire\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Cdiv title=\u0022Protected by Grammarly\u0022\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022AKPWhMU.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/AKPWhMU.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ZjKLzlZ.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/ZjKLzlZ.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022YBH4LE4.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/YBH4LE4.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you need more from specific angles\u00A0just ask again\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-26T12:30:30Z\u0022 title=\u002210/26/2016 12:30  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 26, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DarkFighter\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpeedDaemon","CreatedById":38448,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T13:34:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow are you \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E aligned? How does that alignment change as you burn through your fuel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, are you actually launching that with it starting rotated 45 degrees off of a cardinal direction? Rotating it so that \u0022up\u0022 for the shuttle is 90deg might help some.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Firemetal","CreatedById":164725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T13:47:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh so you mean the nav ball is facing a different angle? Well you usually want to go up and turn over where it says 90 on the nav ball. If you are lifting off and your shuttle keeps spinning out of control, then you want to align the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECOL\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso I see you went with the American design. For beginners, I would suggest going with the Russian Buran design. Much easier to control during ascent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFire\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Harry Rhodan","CreatedById":119953,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T14:18:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRotating the other two vectors helps quite a bit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DarkFighter","CreatedById":168628,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-26T18:12:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk, so I now managed to get to orbit, I rotated it so it flips to the\u00A0east and at the\u00A0start I had to press \u0027s\u0027 all the time. Before that, I had to press \u0027s\u002Bd\u0027 so it was now way easier. As soon as I hit the higher part of the atmosphere, I could fully control the shuttle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0Here are is a picture: (Kerbal Engineer is buggy)\u003Cimg alt=\u0022hrE4T1V.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022562\u0022 src=\u0022http://imgur.com/hrE4T1V.png\u0022 width=\u00221000\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0I had half of the fuel left but Kerbal Engineer was buggy. I fixed that now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 \u00A0 Through your help that Kerbal could possibly be safe. \u00A0For the landing I\u0027ll try a\u00A090km AP and 40km PE. Let\u0027s hope it doesn\u0027t burn up.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-27T15:22:04Z\u0022 title=\u002210/27/2016 03:22  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 27, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by DarkFighter\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DarkFighter","CreatedById":168628,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-27T15:22:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLanded safely at \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}